1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:03,610
(Episode 36)

2
00:00:09,210 --> 00:00:11,280
Since you're putting it that way...

3
00:00:14,150 --> 00:00:15,150
All right.

4
00:00:17,490 --> 00:00:18,490
Very well.

5
00:00:19,460 --> 00:00:21,360
The General Manager
of the Dream's Kitchen...

6
00:00:22,790 --> 00:00:25,160
I'll do it. However,

7
00:00:26,970 --> 00:00:28,100
I have a condition.

8
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:29,700
A condition?

9
00:00:40,350 --> 00:00:43,150
Goodness! What am I going to do?

10
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:45,550
- Gosh.
- Shoot. I dropped it.

11
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:48,220
Who is this solicitor?

12
00:00:48,620 --> 00:00:49,620
Wait.

13
00:00:50,090 --> 00:00:52,820
Jang Mi. What are you doing here?

14
00:00:53,730 --> 00:00:57,100
Hey, if you're going to bump into me,
you could at least apologize.

15
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:00,300
Oh, you're not Jang Mi.

16
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,300
I'm so sorry.

17
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,650
What? You're not Jang Mi.

18
00:01:19,380 --> 00:01:20,990
You're pretending to be Jang Mi.

19
00:01:20,990 --> 00:01:23,090
- You're not Jang Mi.
- What's with this woman?

20
00:01:24,220 --> 00:01:25,220
Jang Mi?

21
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:31,430
Hey! Who on earth is Jang Mi?

22
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:33,030
Tell me.

23
00:01:33,470 --> 00:01:36,470
Why does everyone I meet keep confusing me
with this Jang Mi person?

24
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:38,570
Darn it, this is so frustrating.

25
00:01:39,470 --> 00:01:40,470
I'm sorry.

26
00:01:40,940 --> 00:01:42,410
It's just that you look so much
like my daughter.

27
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:54,220
How can she look so much like my Jang Mi?

28
00:01:54,790 --> 00:01:56,350
Her face is identical.

29
00:01:56,890 --> 00:01:58,690
What are you staring at?
You're creeping me out.

30
00:01:59,260 --> 00:02:00,690
What makes you think
I look like your daughter?

31
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:04,530
I'm sorry. I mistook you for someone else.

32
00:02:04,660 --> 00:02:06,700
You should watch where you're going!
Pay attention!

33
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:14,110
The resemblance is uncanny.

34
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:16,940
What did I just see?

35
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:18,640
Enjoy your meal.

36
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:19,740
- Thank you.
- Bye.

37
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:26,380
Why are you here by yourself?
Did you file for police protection?

38
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:28,290
- Where's Lawyer Kang?
- Tae Sook.

39
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:31,660
Why didn't you tell me
Baek Ho's mother stopped by?

40
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:35,860
- How did you find out?
- How I found out isn't what's important.

41
00:02:37,430 --> 00:02:39,930
So that's why Dad was drinking that day.

42
00:02:40,570 --> 00:02:43,130
What on earth did Baek Ho's mother
say to Dad?

43
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:44,400
What do you think she said?

44
00:02:44,670 --> 00:02:46,770
She told Dad to stop you and him
from seeing each other.

45
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:49,910
But Dad was firm and told her off.

46
00:02:50,210 --> 00:02:54,450
He said Baek Ho's the one chasing Jang Mi,
so she should rein in her own son.

47
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:01,090
Dad, where are you?

48
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:05,190
I just stepped out to run an errand.

49
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:16,030
It's uncanny how much she looks
like Jang Mi.

50
00:03:24,780 --> 00:03:29,450
Jang Mi, you'll never guess who I saw.
Someone who looks like you at the...

51
00:03:29,510 --> 00:03:33,350
I can't tell her
I'm at the Dream Hotel to see CEO Chae.

52
00:03:33,950 --> 00:03:36,850
She'll obviously ask why I was there.

53
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:38,290
Someone who looks just like me?

54
00:03:38,790 --> 00:03:40,330
Where did you see someone like that?

55
00:03:40,690 --> 00:03:43,730
- Just on the street.
- On the street?

56
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:46,760
What? Dad, what's with the random joke?

57
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:48,830
Seriously, I really mean it.

58
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:51,070
Welcome. What can I get for you?

59
00:03:51,470 --> 00:03:55,110
- Dad, a customer's here. I've got to go.
- Really? All right, talk to you later.

60
00:04:01,650 --> 00:04:03,380
All right. What's your condition?

61
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:07,590
As long as you're not asking me
to keep you away from my Seo Rin,

62
00:04:07,890 --> 00:04:09,050
I'll agree to anything.

63
00:04:11,020 --> 00:04:12,220
That's exactly what I'm asking.

64
00:04:13,730 --> 00:04:15,890
I have no desire to work with a stalker.

65
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:20,230
Forgive me if that was too harsh.

66
00:04:20,930 --> 00:04:24,170
But that's how strongly I feel
about Director Ma Seo Rin.

67
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:27,070
I'm just saying this upfront
to avoid any misunderstandings.

68
00:04:29,140 --> 00:04:33,680
I wonder why
you loathe my Seo Rin so much.

69
00:04:34,610 --> 00:04:37,680
All right, enough.
I understand how you feel, Chef Kang.

70
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:42,590
Now that we're clear,
just think over the promotion I offered.

71
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:45,120
I will.

72
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:47,290
Mom, aren't you going to stop
any suspicious people...

73
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:48,590
from entering the hotel?

74
00:04:51,130 --> 00:04:52,300
Jun Ho.

75
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:55,030
If you'll excuse me.

76
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,140
- Jun Ho!
- Seo Rin.

77
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:01,440
Sit down.

78
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:04,880
Why?

79
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:08,380
You need to give Chef Kang some time.

80
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:11,150
Your problem is that you dive in headfirst
when you like someone.

81
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:14,890
If you like someone, just go for it.
Feelings don't last forever, you know.

82
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:18,260
Just be patient for now.
I'll create an opportunity for you.

83
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:21,090
By the way,
did something happen at the hotel?

84
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:22,890
What about being more selective
about our guests?

85
00:05:22,930 --> 00:05:25,460
This time some guy called me Jang Mi.

86
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:26,930
What?

87
00:05:27,530 --> 00:05:28,600
Who would say something like that?

88
00:05:28,730 --> 00:05:32,500
I bumped into this guy in the lobby
who was carrying a bunch of smelly things.

89
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:35,840
And then out of the blue, he's like,
"Jang Mi!" Can you believe that?

90
00:05:36,310 --> 00:05:38,640
Shit. So gross.

91
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:42,550
Don't tell me Oh Bok Gil
has already been here.

92
00:05:48,020 --> 00:05:49,120
What's Oh Jang Mi's current location?

93
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:56,590
What? She's at her shop?

94
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,130
Isn't that Manager Lee,
CEO Chae's assistant?

95
00:06:02,470 --> 00:06:04,970
But why's he asking where my Jang Mi is?

96
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,810
The person you're calling is unavailable.

97
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:17,320
Why won't Oh Bok Gil answer his phone?

98
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:19,980
Why don't he and his family listen to me?

99
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:24,490
I told him to wait for my call,
so why did he come crawling here?

100
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:38,070
Who's he meeting so secretly?

101
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:51,320
This is the guy.

102
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:55,690
(Public Release of Suspect Information,
Name: Park Soon Sun)

103
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:14,470
Go wait. I'll call you.

104
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:15,710
Yes, boss.

105
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,250
"Boss?"

106
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:23,550
Then...

107
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:27,790
Is Ssangkal's boss Manager Lee?

108
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,130
Yes, CEO Chae.

109
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,760
You're asking if I've seen Oh Bok Gil?

110
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:51,580
I'm in the underground parking lot now.
Come down here.

111
00:08:29,110 --> 00:08:33,020
If Ssangkal's boss is Manager Lee, then...

112
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:36,390
it was Manager Lee
who tried to hurt my Jang Mi?

113
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:42,790
<i>- Three bears live in a house</i>
- You're doing great!

114
00:08:43,030 --> 00:08:46,730
<i>Papa Bear, Mama Bear, Baby Bear</i>

115
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:50,600
<i>Papa Bear is chubby</i>

116
00:08:50,940 --> 00:08:54,510
<i>Mama Bear is slender</i>

117
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:58,440
<i>Baby Bear is so cute</i>

118
00:08:58,810 --> 00:09:01,980
<i>We did so well</i>

119
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:04,820
- Bo Ra, you're doing great!
- You're doing so well!

120
00:09:06,650 --> 00:09:08,250
Jang Mi, I'm here.

121
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:17,900
Let's go.

122
00:09:20,970 --> 00:09:23,230
Suk Hee is going to eat fried pork cutlet.

123
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:24,570
Baek Ho's so nice.

124
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,170
Jang Mi is pretty.

125
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:28,140
Mommy, me too!
I want fried pork cutlet too!

126
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,010
- Let's go.
- We'll be back.

127
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,510
- Let's hurry!
- Enjoy your meal.

128
00:09:34,210 --> 00:09:36,750
Here's a whistle.

129
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,750
And this is a taser.

130
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:43,960
There are patrols, but you never know.
Carry these with you when you go out.

131
00:09:45,390 --> 00:09:46,390
Kang Baek Ho.

132
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:48,590
Why are you acting like this toward me?

133
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:55,170
Did you find Oh Bok Gil?

134
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:57,970
He was definitely here.

135
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,010
Why would he leave this and just take off?

136
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:05,040
You don't think
he saw you with Ssangkal, do you?

137
00:10:07,950 --> 00:10:10,920
Darn it. If so, that means he's caught on.

138
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:13,450
That's why he just left this and bolted!

139
00:10:14,050 --> 00:10:15,890
If he knows, I think we're in big trouble.

140
00:10:15,890 --> 00:10:16,990
You think?

141
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:19,520
Find him now!

142
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:22,760
Find him, whatever it takes.
You have to shut him up.

143
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:25,600
Get moving. Now!

144
00:10:26,060 --> 00:10:27,060
Yes, ma'am.

145
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:32,700
Darn it!

146
00:10:34,370 --> 00:10:37,210
Chae Hwa Young.
She was the one behind it all along.

147
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:40,010
How could a person be so cruel?

148
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:42,650
She was wearing a mask this whole time...

149
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:44,780
and trying to kill my Jang Mi?

150
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:46,480
If that's true,

151
00:10:46,650 --> 00:10:50,120
she's the one who did that to my Suk Hee.

152
00:10:50,820 --> 00:10:52,690
Oh my goodness!

153
00:10:54,290 --> 00:10:56,190
(B3 Parking Lot)

154
00:10:56,290 --> 00:10:57,290
Rewind that.

155
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,760
A little more.

156
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:00,870
No, forward.

157
00:11:02,470 --> 00:11:03,470
Stop.

158
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:10,570
(B3 Parking Lot)

159
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:22,650
Wait, I can't just stand here.

160
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:27,430
I have to hurry and expose that evil woman
for who she truly is.

161
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:42,610
(Dad)

162
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:46,410
Please go. Don't give your mother a reason
to come here again.

163
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:49,650
I'm not happy to see you acting like this,
so please, just go.

164
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:51,020
My mom is no match for me.

165
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:54,520
I promise I'll talk her around,
so please don't be out late.

166
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:57,020
And if you do go out, take this with you.

167
00:11:57,890 --> 00:12:00,590
I can take care of myself.
I don't need your help.

168
00:12:01,690 --> 00:12:03,360
That's enough. Please, just go.

169
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:06,200
Please, just be careful.

170
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,730
I'm begging you.

171
00:12:09,530 --> 00:12:11,540
If you get hurt again, I swear...

172
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,700
I'll move right in here.

173
00:12:14,270 --> 00:12:16,170
I'll guard you like a bodyguard
and never leave your side.

174
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,340
I'll go for now.

175
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:22,280
Answer when I call.

176
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:31,720
The person you're calling is unavailable.

177
00:12:54,210 --> 00:12:55,350
There he is!

178
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:57,850
Over there! Grab him!

179
00:13:00,850 --> 00:13:01,850
Darn it!

180
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:07,120
Where do you think you're going, you rat?

181
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,790
You're worse than an animal!

182
00:13:12,060 --> 00:13:13,060
Chae Hwa Young!

183
00:13:21,710 --> 00:13:23,470
Chae Hwa Young! It was you, wasn't it?

184
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:26,340
You tried to kill my Suk Hee
and Jang Mi, didn't you?

185
00:13:26,710 --> 00:13:31,020
- Why? Just tell me why!
- In this situation, being curious...

186
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:32,780
will only be your downfall.

187
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:36,320
Don't you realize that your curiosity
is just rushing you to your grave?

188
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:38,260
Get rid of him.

189
00:13:38,790 --> 00:13:41,690
Now that he knows everything,
there's no other choice.

190
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,400
You...

191
00:13:54,510 --> 00:13:59,040
You approached Tae Pyung from the start
to kill Suk Hee and Jang Mi, right?

192
00:13:59,210 --> 00:14:02,580
You witch! How could you deceive us,
hiding behind a mask?

193
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:07,150
Go to the police! Go and tell them
why you did that to Suk Hee,

194
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:11,220
and why you tried to kill Jang Mi.
Tell them everything.

195
00:14:11,290 --> 00:14:12,390
Let go of me!

196
00:14:12,390 --> 00:14:15,060
I said, let go of me!

197
00:14:49,890 --> 00:14:53,500
I'm thinking of recommending
the young, talented Chef Kang Jun Ho...

198
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:56,470
to be the general manager
overseeing the Dream's Kitchen.

199
00:14:56,870 --> 00:14:58,700
What is she up to?

200
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:01,540
Jun Ho!

201
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,740
My mom finally gave us
her permission to date!

202
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:10,110
What on earth is she thinking?

203
00:15:11,450 --> 00:15:12,750
Where are you going? Let me come with you.

204
00:15:14,390 --> 00:15:15,420
To the market.

205
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:17,150
The fish market.

206
00:15:17,390 --> 00:15:20,360
I can't stand smelly places.

207
00:15:20,590 --> 00:15:21,590
Perfect.

208
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:23,130
Don't follow me.

209
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,410
First, it was that dim-witted old woman,

210
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:37,880
and today it was some guy
carrying a bunch of smelly things.

211
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:42,780
Just how much does that woman look like me
that everyone keeps calling me Jang Mi?

212
00:15:44,550 --> 00:15:46,420
Shit! This is so aggravating.

213
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:23,690
Bring the car around.

214
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,320
Yes.

215
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:38,800
I told you to pull up
the lobby's CCTV footage.

216
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:40,840
Didn't you hear what I said?

217
00:16:41,310 --> 00:16:42,410
May I ask why?

218
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:44,610
Do I have to explain why to you?

219
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:48,710
I told you I need to find that riffraff
who came in carrying those smelly things.

220
00:16:48,780 --> 00:16:50,280
How many times do I have to repeat myself?

221
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:57,590
(First Floor Lobby Elevator)

222
00:17:00,690 --> 00:17:03,830
Wait, stop! Right there!

223
00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:05,130
Zoom in.

224
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,700
Come on, hurry up!

225
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:09,870
Okay.

226
00:17:17,410 --> 00:17:19,480
"Suk Hee's Side Dishes."

227
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,380
And the address is right here.

228
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:25,180
You are so dead.

229
00:17:25,950 --> 00:17:26,950
Shit.

230
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:35,030
What's the plan?

231
00:17:36,290 --> 00:17:39,000
- What about the security cameras?
- When I was in the control room earlier,

232
00:17:39,260 --> 00:17:41,670
I had them turn off all the cameras
in the underground parking lot.

233
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:46,070
The only thing is that we'll need to check
the dashcams of any cars parked nearby.

234
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:48,110
Take care of that first
and leave no trace.

235
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,470
Two hours should be enough, right?

236
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:53,410
- Yes, ma'am.
- Good.

237
00:17:53,780 --> 00:17:56,610
I'll text you an address.
When you're finished, meet me there.

238
00:17:57,850 --> 00:18:00,450
Do you have a plan for how to handle it?

239
00:18:03,420 --> 00:18:06,160
Then I'll take care of things here
and catch up with you.

240
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,280
That looks delicious.

241
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:33,850
Just a moment, please.

242
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:37,020
- All right.
- Please, enjoy, Chairman.

243
00:18:41,590 --> 00:18:43,590
- You have some too.
- Okay.

244
00:18:44,830 --> 00:18:48,330
You're not upset
that I dragged you here, are you?

245
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:50,030
Upset? Not at all.

246
00:18:50,330 --> 00:18:51,900
It's good to eat out
every once in a while.

247
00:18:55,670 --> 00:18:56,710
By the way,

248
00:18:56,710 --> 00:19:01,180
I think we should give
Geum Soon a raise, Chairman.

249
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:04,350
That's not your place to say.
CEO Chae will handle it.

250
00:19:04,780 --> 00:19:07,580
Oh my. You really have no idea, do you?

251
00:19:08,350 --> 00:19:12,560
What CEO Chae and Director Ma
did to poor Geum Soon.

252
00:19:17,860 --> 00:19:19,260
Please have some of the porridge.

253
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:22,570
- You haven't eaten a thing...
- Mrs. Yang!

254
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:28,310
- Did you machine-wash this?
- Of course not.

255
00:19:28,740 --> 00:19:30,640
This isn't my first day on the job.

256
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:34,140
The sheen is gone from the blouse.

257
00:19:35,210 --> 00:19:37,680
What's wrong? Is it not to your liking?

258
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:41,490
Where is your head at these days,
Mrs. Yang?

259
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:44,720
I told you not to put MSG
in my food, didn't I?

260
00:19:44,820 --> 00:19:47,220
Ma'am, I didn't add any.

261
00:19:47,590 --> 00:19:49,590
Who in their right mind
puts MSG in porridge?

262
00:19:50,090 --> 00:19:52,700
I even used homemade soy sauce
and put it on the side for you.

263
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:54,600
Are you calling me a liar?

264
00:19:55,130 --> 00:19:57,570
- Taste it yourself.
- Shit.

265
00:19:57,830 --> 00:20:01,340
Are you doing this to spite my mom and me?

266
00:20:01,540 --> 00:20:05,410
You've worked here so long,
you think you can walk all over us now?

267
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:09,650
- That's not true.
- Seo Rin, don't raise your voice.

268
00:20:10,510 --> 00:20:12,580
If that's going to be your attitude,
Mrs. Yang,

269
00:20:12,580 --> 00:20:14,320
we'll just have to respond in kind.

270
00:20:14,820 --> 00:20:16,220
I'm docking it from your pay.

271
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:18,660
To replace this blouse,

272
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:22,060
it would cost her
several months' salary, Mom.

273
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:24,930
Ma'am.

274
00:20:24,930 --> 00:20:25,930
Director Ma.

275
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:30,930
I swear I would never do that.
This is so unfair!

276
00:20:35,310 --> 00:20:37,340
I'm the one who put it in the porridge.

277
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:40,180
Geum Soon,

278
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:42,350
that's what you get for disrespecting me.

279
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:47,720
Surely, Geum Soon wouldn't do
such a thing on purpose.

280
00:20:48,450 --> 00:20:50,150
She must have felt so wrongfully accused.

281
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:55,590
CEO Chae can be so unreasonable.

282
00:21:03,670 --> 00:21:05,240
- You're home?
- Yes.

283
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:12,080
Geum Soon who dares to mess with me...

284
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:14,110
and Hwa Young and Seo Rin
who treat me and my daughter like rats.

285
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:15,510
They'll all get a taste of their medicine.

286
00:21:16,580 --> 00:21:20,120
I believe in an eye for an eye.

287
00:21:27,090 --> 00:21:29,230
- You're home?
- Yes.

288
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:32,130
Looks like Jun Ho isn't home yet?

289
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:36,870
- Mom, I am so disappointed in you.
- Are we on this again?

290
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:40,240
Was it really so wrong of me
to go to Jang Mi's house?

291
00:21:40,300 --> 00:21:43,540
You're a lawyer.
How can you be so prejudiced?

292
00:21:43,610 --> 00:21:44,710
Hey, Baek Ho.

293
00:21:45,510 --> 00:21:47,640
Your mom only wants what's best for you.

294
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,650
Do you think she did it
to give you a hard time?

295
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:51,820
How is that for my own good?

296
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,950
Jang Mi is so hurt
that she won't even see me anymore.

297
00:21:54,580 --> 00:21:57,920
And you and Dad don't even know
the first thing about her.

298
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,160
So why on earth are you doing this?

299
00:21:59,590 --> 00:22:01,220
Do you hate seeing me happy that much?

300
00:22:02,290 --> 00:22:04,900
That's not how you should take it, son.

301
00:22:06,830 --> 00:22:07,860
Hey!

302
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:10,600
Just leave him be.

303
00:22:11,670 --> 00:22:15,370
He's completely blinded by love.
Nothing we say will get through to him.

304
00:22:17,770 --> 00:22:19,040
Good grief.

305
00:22:19,340 --> 00:22:20,340
I'm home.

306
00:22:20,780 --> 00:22:22,150
Jun Ho, welcome home.

307
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:29,520
You don't look so good.

308
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:32,820
- Is something on your mind?
- No.

309
00:22:33,490 --> 00:22:36,430
Actually, CEO Chae offered me
a position as the general manager.

310
00:22:37,590 --> 00:22:39,160
Oh, really?

311
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:41,430
Jun Ho.

312
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:45,100
Just the other day you were talking
about quitting,

313
00:22:45,370 --> 00:22:47,340
and now you're suddenly getting
a promotion to the general manager?

314
00:22:48,570 --> 00:22:49,740
How did that happen?

315
00:22:50,540 --> 00:22:52,140
Hwa Young, thank you.

316
00:22:52,710 --> 00:22:55,780
You must have promoted him
because you know he's my son.

317
00:22:56,750 --> 00:23:01,080
What do you mean?
She must have recognized his talent.

318
00:23:01,350 --> 00:23:04,090
- Right?
- I wonder why she's suddenly doing this.

319
00:23:05,420 --> 00:23:08,960
Just say thank you and accept it. Got it?

320
00:23:08,990 --> 00:23:12,600
It's not some mom-and-pop shop.
Promotions are based on merit.

321
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:20,640
Professor, I'm at that resort
you mentioned.

322
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,940
It's as private as you said.

323
00:23:23,570 --> 00:23:24,940
I want to see you now.

324
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:26,680
You are coming, aren't you?

325
00:23:27,980 --> 00:23:28,980
What is it?

326
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:31,750
- Who was that? Why so shocked?
- What?

327
00:23:33,020 --> 00:23:34,120
Well...

328
00:23:34,420 --> 00:23:37,220
It's from school. I completely forgot.

329
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,960
I must have gotten the deadline
for submitting grades mixed up.

330
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:43,590
Does that mean you have to go
to the university now?

331
00:23:44,490 --> 00:23:45,600
Yes.

332
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:48,130
Oh my...

333
00:23:48,830 --> 00:23:50,800
Good grief.

334
00:23:52,140 --> 00:23:54,810
I don't know where his head is these days.

335
00:23:55,510 --> 00:23:59,110
He gets calls from his teaching assistant
at all hours.

336
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:00,180
Really?

337
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:04,080
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

338
00:24:09,290 --> 00:24:11,560
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

339
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:16,360
So this must be the place.

340
00:24:20,260 --> 00:24:24,770
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

341
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:26,340
No way. Is that her?

342
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:30,570
Is that really his daughter?
The one named Jang Mi or whatever?

343
00:24:31,980 --> 00:24:34,910
How much could she possibly look like me
for him to mistake her for his daughter?

344
00:24:36,450 --> 00:24:38,050
This is so insulting.

345
00:24:39,180 --> 00:24:41,120
I have to see for myself.

346
00:24:47,060 --> 00:24:48,060
Welcome.

347
00:24:56,230 --> 00:24:57,300
There it is.

348
00:24:58,740 --> 00:25:00,440
I have a missed call from Dad.

349
00:25:36,940 --> 00:25:38,110
Hello? Dad?

350
00:25:41,910 --> 00:25:42,950
Dad?

351
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:45,150
Dad, what's wrong? Are you hurt?

352
00:25:47,950 --> 00:25:48,990
Jang Mi.

353
00:25:50,490 --> 00:25:51,550
Listen to me carefully.

354
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,530
The one who did that to your mother...

355
00:25:58,130 --> 00:25:59,130
and you...

356
00:26:00,230 --> 00:26:01,230
You...

357
00:26:03,470 --> 00:26:04,570
Ssangkal...

358
00:26:41,870 --> 00:26:45,180
Dad! What's going on?

359
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:49,010
Dad, what's wrong? Tell me.

360
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:08,130
(The First Man)

361
00:27:08,330 --> 00:27:11,230
Oh Bok Gil,
if you'd only kept your mouth shut,

362
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:13,240
none of this would have happened.

363
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,410
Your life was cut short...

364
00:27:15,470 --> 00:27:18,910
because you just had to meddle
by taking in Jung Suk Hee and Oh Jang Mi.

365
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:21,640
Twins? There are two of me?

366
00:27:21,810 --> 00:27:24,680
What? You went to that side dish shop?

367
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:26,420
When do you think you'll get here?

368
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:27,820
I'm almost there.

369
00:27:28,250 --> 00:27:30,690
Professor Kang should be
passing by here any second now.

370
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:34,420
Oh Bok Gil, don't you blame me.

371
00:27:36,490 --> 00:27:38,500
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
